{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/research-briefs/2019-06-29-how-to-improve-park-experiences-for-transgender-visitors/","webpackCompilationHash":"","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"53f796fa-3cf6-5232-b1dd-c2ecfd0e4425","html":"<p><span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 2048px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 54.15407854984895%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"locker-room\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/9da0cf901394a5424302bd8eb8161efb/2b40c/locker-room.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/9da0cf901394a5424302bd8eb8161efb/ab422/locker-room.jpg 512w,\n/static/9da0cf901394a5424302bd8eb8161efb/1f853/locker-room.jpg 1024w,\n/static/9da0cf901394a5424302bd8eb8161efb/2b40c/locker-room.jpg 2048w,\n/static/9da0cf901394a5424302bd8eb8161efb/986f8/locker-room.jpg 3072w,\n/static/9da0cf901394a5424302bd8eb8161efb/8789c/locker-room.jpg 3972w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 2048px) 100vw, 2048px\"\n      />\n  </span></p>\n<h2>How can park spaces be made more welcoming for transgender visitors?</h2>\n<p>Start by assessing the experience of spaces that are often highly gendered â€“ e.g. bathrooms, pools, showers and locker rooms. These spaces are where transgender visitors are likely to feel the most uncomfortable. Prioritize privacy; ensure your bathrooms have stall doors, showers have curtains, etc.</p>\n<h2>What are ways parks and rec pros can promote inclusive park programming?</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Offer co-ed and non-gendered sports.</li>\n<li>Create transgender-focused programming to help these visitors learn athletic skills that were not a part of their birth-gender upbringing.</li>\n<li>Reach out to your local transgender community to see if there are unmet needs.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Where can I learn more?</h2>\n<p>Learn from your peers! Start or join the conversation about more inclusive parks at <a href=\"https://community.muniparks.com/\">community.muniparks.com</a>.</p>\n<h2>Recommended Reading:</h2>\n<ul class=\"sources\">                            \n\t<li>\n\t    <span class=\"label label--soft\">\n        <img src=\"https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=https://js.sagamorepub.com/jpra/\"> \n    \t<span>JPRA</span>   \n\t    </span>\n\t    &ldquo;<a href=\"https://js.sagamorepub.com/jpra/article/view/7363\">Dreaming About Access: The Experiences of Transgender Individuals in Public Recreation</a>&rdquo;<img src=\"/img/offsite_black.png\" class=\"off-site-link\" alt=\"offsite link\">\n\t</li>                     \n</ul>","frontmatter":{"date":"July 02, 2019","image":{"childImageSharp":{"resize":{"src":"/static/9da0cf901394a5424302bd8eb8161efb/81ef8/locker-room.jpg","height":650,"width":1200}}},"title":"How to improve park experiences for transgender visitors","label":"Research Brief","description":"Everyone should feel comfortable at the park. What are some practical ways you can make that happen?","tags":["transgender"],"author":"Ryan McKnight"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"id":"53f796fa-3cf6-5232-b1dd-c2ecfd0e4425"}}}